FBIS4-8811 "dreeu074_i_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Events in Gorazde -- 15 April Events in Gorazde -- 15 April UN Observers Attacked, One Killed LD1504173894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 15 Apr 94 LD1504173894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpt] We have just received another report from Gorazde. In addition to fierce attacks on Gorazde, its unarmed civilians and brave defenders of the town, the chetniks have also been attacking the UN military observers in the town. UN military observers were attacked by the chetniks at about 1700 in the Jabuka Sedlo mountain pass area while they were inspecting the demarcation lines in the area. According to unconfirmed reports, the chetniks killed one UN monitor and seriously wounded a translator in this perfidious assassination. [passage omitted]
